==历史==
===在二战中===
====日方====
{{Main|慰安妇}}
“慰安妇”是性奴隶案例。该词汇指代在二战日本帝国军队占领区，妇女被迫成为妓女以满足侵略者的现象。对于人数的估算多少不一，有的日本学者估算为20,000人<!-- <ref name="AWF_CW" /> -->，而有的中国学者估算为410,000人<ref>{{cite book |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=W2nU1Xu0XdkC&pg=PA88 |title=Sino-Japanese Relations: Facing the Past, Looking to the Future? |first=Caroline |last=Rose |page=88 |publisher=Taylor & Francis |date=31 August 2004 |access-date=2014-07-10 |archive-date=2021-02-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225064512/https://books.google.com/books?id=W2nU1Xu0XdkC&pg=PA88 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。该数字仍在研究和争议当中。绝大多数慰安妇来自朝鲜、中国和其它[[大东亚共荣圈|大东亚共荣圈]]占领地。她们常常被诱拐、或欺骗来入行<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indonesia-ottawa.org/information/details.php?type=news_copy&id=3835 |title=Embassy of Indonesia Ottawa, Canada |accessdate=2007-10-26 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070729234216/http://www.indonesia-ottawa.org/information/details.php?type=news_copy&id=3835 |archivedate=2007-07-29 }}</ref><ref name="Fackler2007">{{cite news | first=Martin | last=Fackler | title=No Apology for Sex Slavery, Japan’s Prime Minister Says | date=6 March 2007 | url=http://www.nytimes.com/2007/03/06/world/asia/06japan.html | work=The New York Times | accessdate=23 March 2007 | archive-date=2021-03-08 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308145647/https://www.nytimes.com/2007/03/06/world/asia/06japan.html | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Abequestions2007">{{cite news | title=Abe questions sex slave 'coercion' | date=2007-03-02 | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/6411471.stm | work=BBC News | accessdate=23 March 2007 | archive-date=2021-02-06 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206205833/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/6411471.stm | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Japanparty2007">{{cite news | title=Japan party probes sex slave use | date=2007-03-08 | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/6431011.stm | work=BBC News | accessdate=23 March 2007 | archive-date=2007-03-12 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070312064206/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/6431011.stm | dead-url=no }}</ref>。很多妇女被强奸致死，或是被折磨而死，如将乳房切割或撕裂腹部<ref>{{cite book |author=Peter Li |title=Japanese war crimes: the search for justice |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=wdy6adh3rXQC&pg=PA45 |accessdate=8 March 2011 |year=2003 |publisher=Transaction Publishers |isbn=978-0-7658-0890-5 |pages=45– |archive-date=2016-04-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160425154138/https://books.google.com/books?id=wdy6adh3rXQC&pg=PA45 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。根据1995年联合国人权委员会的报告<ref>{{cite web |first=Karen |last=Parker |authorlink=Karen Parker (lawyer) |url=http://www.guidetoaction.org/parker/c95-11.html |title=U.N. Speech on Comfort Women – Karen Parker, J.D. speaking on sexual slavery |publisher=Guidetoaction.org |accessdate=2011-03-08 |archive-date=2010-12-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101217202856/http://www.guidetoaction.org/parker/c95-11.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，性奴“每天被强奸约10次（按下限估算），每周五天；可以推算，每名‘慰安妇’每周被强奸约50次，或每年2,500次。以三年计算，慰安妇平均会被强奸7,500次”。

====德方====
二战期间，德方在集中营内开设妓院（Lagerbordell），为受降者服务。在[[拉文斯布吕克集中营|拉文斯布吕克集中营]]中，妇女被迫卖淫<ref>''War crimes against women: prosecution in international war crimes tribunals'' Kelly Dawn Askin page 72</ref>，为将士服务的妓院（Wehrmachtsbordell）常常是被德军没收的老妓院或是旅馆。妓院常常会散佈性病。在被管控的妓院中，妓女们不得不频繁体检，防治性病。

据估算，在第三帝国时期，沦陷国家和地区中约有至少34,140名妇女被迫卖淫<ref name="Herbermann">''The Blessed Abyss: Inmate #6582 in Ravensbruck Concentration Prison for Women'' by Nanda Herbermann</ref>。在欧洲被占领地区，当地妇女常常被迫卖淫<ref name=Wprost>Numer: 17/18/2007 Wprost "Seksualne Niewolnice III Rzeszy"</ref>。1941年5月2日，波兰流亡政府外交部长发函，称大批纳粹扫荡波兰城市，目的是抓小姑娘给德军将士享受<ref name="Wprost"/>。妇女常常试图逃跑，挪威至少有一次已知的大规模行动<ref name="Wprost"/>。

===白奴===
十九世纪到二十世纪早期，在英语国家中白奴（"white slavery"）指代对白人妇女的性奴役。这与中东[[后宫_(伊斯兰)|后宫]]中被奴役的妇女有关，例如所谓的[[切尔克斯人|切尔克斯人]]美女<ref>Linda Frost, ''Never one nation: freaks, savages, and whiteness in U.S. popular culture, 1850–1877,'' University of Minnesota Press, 2005, p. 68-88.</ref>。该词汇后来逐渐演变成为对妓女的委婉语<ref>In the US this usage became prominent around 1909: "a group of books and pamphlets appeared announcing a startling claim: a pervasive and depraved conspiracy was at large in the land, brutally trapping and seducing American girls into lives of enforced prostitution, or 'white slavery.' These white slave narratives, or white-slave tracts, began to circulate around 1909." Mark Thomas Connelly, ''The Response to Prostitution in the Progressive Era'', University of North Carolina Press, 1980, p.114</ref>。该词汇在对未成年人进行性剥削上特别常用，暗指儿童的年青女孩无法决定自己的命运。

在英国维多利亚时代，《蓓尔美街报》竞选记者威廉·托马斯·斯特德花了£5买了一名13岁女孩，这等于一名劳工一个月的工资。（''参见''伊莱扎·阿姆斯特朗案件）十九世纪八十年代，英国对于“拐卖妇女”的[[道德恐慌|道德恐慌]]达到了最高峰。那时，“白奴”成为公共道德和文人墨客的自然攻击目标。接踵而至的呼声迫使议会立法废奴。议会通过了《1885年刑法修正案》，将[[最低合法性交年龄|最低合法性交年龄]]从13岁抬高到了16岁。<ref>Cecil Adeams, "The Straight Dope: [http://www.straightdope.com/columns/read/1302/was-there-really-such-a-thing-as-white-slavery Was there really such a thing as "white slavery"?] {{Wayback|url=http://www.straightdope.com/columns/read/1302/was-there-really-such-a-thing-as-white-slavery |date=20180923163352 }}" January 15, 1999.</ref>

随后，美国在二十世纪早期也出现了类似的恐慌，在1910年达到高潮。芝加哥检察官声称(没有给出细节)国际犯罪团伙正在欧洲拐卖女孩，将她们送进芝加哥的妓院里卖淫。这导致了道德恐慌，使得美国在1910年通过了《曼恩法案》。法案禁止以淫荡目的跨州运动女性。它的主要目的是控制卖淫和道德堕落。<ref>Cecil Adams, ''op. cit.''</ref>

纽约[[埃利斯島|埃利斯島]]移民检查官负责检查来自欧洲的妓女，但检察官表示十分受挫，因为她们对于问答而言常常“撒谎”、“善于胡编”。他们常常被指责受到虚假地址的糊弄，接受了不完整的应答。检察官海伦·布里斯调查了纽约田德隆区的几个家庭，发现在二十世纪早期就出现了妓院。她编撰了妓院列表，包含了所有人和居住人<ref name="Moloney2012">{{cite book|author=Deirdre M. Moloney|title=National Insecurities: Immigrants and U.S. Deportation Policy since 1882|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=GDHpGDVfQE4C&pg=PA62|accessdate=28 September 2013|date=7 May 2012|publisher=Univ of North Carolina Press|isbn=978-0-8078-8261-0|pages=62–|archive-date=2016-06-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160624032210/https://books.google.com/books?id=GDHpGDVfQE4C&pg=PA62|dead-url=no}}</ref>。纽约检查主任在1907年写报道，为玩忽职守的罪名辩护，称公众没必要“恐慌”，他已经尽力筛查来自欧洲的妓女，特别是未婚女性<ref name="Gardner2009">p. 69.</ref>。移民总监在1914年报道中称许多妓女会刻意嫁给美国人来骗取国籍。他称：欧洲妓女“嫁给品行不端的家伙”并非难事。

美国的华裔移民不算在白奴之内，这些活动在华裔社区内算为犯罪。在美国文化中，音乐剧《蜜莉姑娘》中对华裔妓院进行了特写，并将其列为“白奴”。帮派电影《双龙大火拼》<ref>''Prime Cut''</ref>里中西部白奴像牛羊一样被出售。

===阿拉伯贩奴===
{{main|伊斯蘭世界奴隸貿易}}
直到二十世纪为止，奴隶交易，包括性奴<ref>{{cite web|title=Religions – Islam: Slavery in Islam|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/religion/religions/islam/history/slavery_7.shtml|accessdate=2012-07-08|publisher=Bbc.co.uk|archive-date=2009-05-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090521234122/http://www.bbc.co.uk/religion/religions/islam/history/slavery_7.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref>，在[[中东|中东]]某些地区泛滥成灾<ref>{{cite web|title=Mauritania made slavery illegal last month|url=http://www.saiia.org.za/modules.php?op=modload&name=News&file=article&sid=1141|accessdate=2016-01-21|publisher=The South African Institute of International Affairs|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071028085128/http://www.saiia.org.za/modules.php?op=modload&name=News&file=article&sid=1141|archivedate=2007-10-28|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。这些奴隶主要来自[[撒哈拉以南非洲|撒哈拉以南非洲]]、[[北高加索|北高加索]]地区（以[[切尔克斯人|切尔克斯人]]为主）<ref>[http://chnm.gmu.edu/lostmuseum/lm/311/ "Horrible Traffic in Circassian Women—Infanticide in Turkey,"] {{Wayback|url=http://chnm.gmu.edu/lostmuseum/lm/311/ |date=20150628111757 }} New York Daily Times, August 6, 1856</ref>、[[中亚|中亚]]（以[[突厥人|突厥人]]为主）、中欧和东欧（以''[[萨卡里巴|萨卡里巴]]''为主）<ref>{{cite web|title=Soldier Khan|url=http://www.avalanchepress.com/Soldier_Khan.php|accessdate=2012-07-08|publisher=Avalanchepress.com|archive-date=2012-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120801113659/http://www.avalanchepress.com/Soldier_Khan.php|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在十六世纪到十九世纪期间，[[巴巴里海盗|巴巴里-{}-海盗]]也从西欧掠走了125万名奴隶<ref name="researchnews.osu.edu">{{Cite web|title=When Europeans Were Slaves: Research Suggests White Slavery Was Much More Common Than Previously Believed|url=http://researchnews.osu.edu/archive/whtslav.htm|accessdate=2020-11-25|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110725220038/http://researchnews.osu.edu/archive/whtslav.htm|archivedate=2011-07-25|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name="Davis, Robert 1999">Davis, Robert. ''Christian Slaves, Muslim Masters: White Slavery in the Mediterranean, the Barbary Coast and Italy, 1500–1800''.Based on "records for 27,233 voyages that set out to obtain slaves for the Americas". Stephen Behrendt, "Transatlantic Slave Trade", ''Africana: The Encyclopedia of the African and African American Experience'' (New York: Basic Civitas Books, 1999), ISBN 0-465-00071-1.</ref>。

